# Zero-Based Indexing 0️⃣

Access elements using their **index**, which starts from **0**.
`marks[0]` is the first element, `marks[4]` is the last (for size 5).

## Initialization
```c
// All at once
int scores[3] = {90, 85, 95};

// One by one
scores[0] = 90;
scores[1] = 85;
```

> ⚠️ **Memory Safety:** accessing `scores[10]` in a size 3 array leads to **undefined behavior** (garbage value or crash)!

# Grids and Matrices ▦

You can have arrays of arrays! The most common is the **2D array**.

## Declaration
```c
// 3 rows, 4 columns
int matrix[3][4];
```

## Accessing
`matrix[row][col]`

```c
int grid[2][2] = {
    {1, 2}, // Row 0
    {3, 4}  // Row 1
};
int val = grid[1][0]; // Gets 3
```

